Git History:

1. Linus Torvalds started developing Git in 2005 after an open source SCM (source-control management) software
	by the name "BitKeeper" was withdrawn from free usage by its creator.

2. Linus wanted to create an SCM with strong safeguards against any kind of corruption.

3. Git was created in a month by Linus and he used It to release the new linux kernel.
